data.name: Stuffed Tomatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy tomatoes filled with a savory mix of rice, herbs, and gooey cheese, baked to perfection.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the tops off the tomatoes and scoop out the insides using a spoon, creating a hollow center.
In a bowl, mix the cooked rice, shredded cheese, chopped fresh basil, olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder until well combined.
Stuff each hollowed tomato with the rice mixture, pressing down gently to pack it in.
Place the stuffed tomatoes in a baking dish and bake for 25-30 minutes or until the tomatoes are tender and the cheese is melted and bubbly.
Remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving.
